    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="416"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d416">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 822.51/185.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Hartman</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 25, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your August 22. On account of the grave disturbance to all the money markets of
                    the world and the almost total suspension of credits, the Department does not
                    feel that the present is a propitious time to assist Ecuador in obtaining a
                    loan.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
